            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <date>September 8. 5611</date> A.M.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I was ordered to send you the<lb/> following for insertion in the
                next <sic>number</sic><lb/> of the Occident, the bill for insertion fees to<lb/> be
                    <sic>send</sic> to <persName>Simpson &amp; Beckel</persName> in
                    <placeName>Albany</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The Congregation Anshe Emeth</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">in <placeName>Albany N. Y.</placeName></p>
            <p>For consequence of the ill and unjust<lb/> treatment of a party of the Congregation
                Beth El<lb/> in <placeName>Albany</placeName> to the <persName>Rev. Dr.
                    Wise</persName> 56 members<lb/> of this Congregation which were joined by
                21<lb/> Israelites, who had been no members of a<lb/> Synagogue previously to this
                time constituted<lb/> a new Congregation under the name of Anshe<lb/> Emeth (men of
                truth). This congregation is now<lb/> actively employed to build a Synagogue and
                a<lb/> school house, which will be <sic>complesed</sic> as soon<lb/> as
                    <date>Shebnoth</date> next. At a regular meeting of<lb/> this congregation
                    (<date>September</date>
                <add>?</add>) the following officers were<lb/> elected: <persName>Mr Joseph
                    Spoiborg</persName> Parnass, <persName>Mr. F<lb/> Schulz</persName> Cashier,
                    <persName>Mr. Maier Stern</persName>, <persName>A. West-<lb/>heimer</persName>,
                and <persName>T. Klugman</persName> Trustees, <persName>D. I. Levy</persName><lb/>
                Shamesh. The <persName>Rev. Dr. Wise</persName>, who resigned<lb/> his office in the
                Congregation Beth El, was<lb/> then unanimously elected Rabbi of this<lb/>
                Congregation. The whole chair went over to the<lb/> new Congregation, consequently
                the divine service<lb/> now in a saloon furnished to that purpose, is<lb/> held in
                the same solemn manner as formerly in<lb/> the Synagogue Beth El. The school of
                    <persName>Dr. Wise</persName><lb/> continues to exist with nearly the same
                    <sic>numbre</sic><lb/> of pupils as before. All difficulties between the</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>two Congregations were <sic>peacably</sic> settled and all<lb/> law suits dropped.
                Brotherly feelings will soon<lb/> return.”</p>
            <p>I have to say something against your articles<lb/> though you did not yet come to the
                main point;<lb/> but since I think to see you next week in<lb/>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, I do not write about it,<lb/> I cannot answer
                    <persName>Mr. Millers</persName> I have too<lb/> much work on hand.</p>
            <p>I am sorry to hear that you are unwell and<lb/> I hope to find you well next week. I
                shall<lb/> not go away this time as fast or lately, having<lb/> to talk a great deal
                with you.</p>
            <p>I feel now very well, that I am relieved of all<lb/> domestic troubles, and I hope
                now to settle with<lb/> all my literary opponents. If I happen to<lb/> be
                    <add>שבת</add> in <placeName>Phi</placeName> I should like to lecture in
                one<lb/> of the Synagogues in the german language;<lb/> and if possible I would
                speak in the afternoon<lb/> on some subject in the english language. I<lb/> think to
                be with you <add>פרשת לך לך</add>.</p>
            <p>I beg your pardon for my confused<lb/> writing, I have too much work on hand</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Sincerely yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Dr Wise</persName>
            </p>
